      <div class="msgContentFrame">It's a pathing bug. Mobs have a set area in which they can be engaged (largely so you can run away and to prevent excessive training, or so I would guess), but for one reason or another that area isn't necessarily the same size as the area they can physically roam at least as far as the bug is concerned. When you engage the mob the bug makes the servers think the enemy is out of place and tries to reset it which is what causes its HP to regen. It can be especially frustrating when you <b>are</b> in the right spot, but the mob has a knock-back ability that sends you flying outside of the designated area prompting the reset anyway. <br /> <br />Of course on the bright side, if the enemy isn't terribly difficult it can be a good way to rack up extra SP as long as you don't lose claim to it. And after it resets it should lose all aggro as long as you don't attack it again so it's also a good opportunity to run away if you think you might die.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><span class="sm"><u>FFXI (Retired)</u> <br />Naiya | Mithra | Windurst | Rank 10 | 1st Lieutenant | Ragnarok <br /><b>WAR:</b> 75 <b>MNK:</b> 75 <b>SAM:</b> 66 <br /><b>RotZ:</b> O | <b>CoP:</b> O | <b>ToAU:</b> O |  <b>Apoch Nigh:</b> O <br /> <br /><u>WoW</u> <br />Naiyah | B.Elf | 80 Rogue | Stormscale <br />Doubleday | B.Elf | 80 Paladin | Stormscale</span> <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/367614.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /></div></div>
