      <div class="msgContentFrame">The term I have seen is EoRR: End-of-Rope Regen. <br /> <br />When monsters leave their comfort zone, they tend to run back toward the center while healing, much like the Looney Tunes comedy bit Where <a href="HTTP://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foghorn_Leghorn" rel="external nofollow" title="en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Foghorn_Leghorn">Foghorn Leghorn</a> always stands 'just beyond' the dog's length of rope, so he can see the dog choke itself when at its limit. <br /> <br />While some players are frustrated by this causing monsters that just don't die, Some players consider this advantageous, as a party could consistently reach 500 sp by gauging how long the monster's &quot;rope&quot; is, positioning the team at the edge of this range, and repeatedly pulling to the end of the 'rope', causing repeated regeneration, and longer battles and therefore more sp each battle.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>-------------------- <br />FFXIV: Lalafell Battlemage Hybrid (Rabanastre) <br /> <br />FFXI: 75 Taru-Taru RDM/SMN, WHM, DRK, NIN (Retired, Bismarck) <br /><a href="HTTP://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?13780" rel="external" title="ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?13780">Duuude</a>  <br /> <br />WOW: 60 Undead Warlock (Retired, Durotan) <br /> <br /><img src="http://common.zam.com/xivsigs/325573.png" alt="Signature Image" border="0" /> <br /></div></div>
